{"TopicId":218360,"ForumId":139,"TopicTitle":"KSP2 Keybinds","CreatedByName":"Intercept Games","CreatedById":210281,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-11T23:42:54Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Intercept Games","CreatedById":210281,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-11T23:42:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image\u0022 href=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_12/image.png.382941b4f42105a5ddab997e84ebc0a8.png\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221124\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022png\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221124\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 data-unique=\u0022n1fpvaup2\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 alt=\u0022image.png\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_12/image.thumb.png.df62211a2e6cc0b4adc0cac85680d72a.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image\u0022 href=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_12/image.png.40560ad41c98608dddaaf9d9cb5fad44.png\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221125\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022png\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221125\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.33\u0022 data-unique=\u00221k0l6aouq\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 alt=\u0022image.png\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_12/image.thumb.png.e9ebaa8fdd2e562be5b6f893a5207037.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image\u0022 href=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_12/image.png.6cc2fbfd500c84112686da3d8bc74315.png\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221126\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022png\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221126\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.33\u0022 data-unique=\u0022oj31i1x00\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 alt=\u0022image.png\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_12/image.thumb.png.6be8c536e641989125991899556e4703.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLast updated: 12/18/2023\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee notes below.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dakota","CreatedById":225122,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-12T00:18:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003ENotes:\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nThe Quickload key (Default: F9) actually has two keybind options available, Quickload and Quickload (Hold). There is an additional option in the settings that allows you to switch between the two. The Quickload (Hold) keybind will include a short pause before quickloading if enabled\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nCertain Camera Controls (Numpad, ArrowKeys) only work while in Capture Camera mode\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nF4 to toggle labels also works during EVA\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nThe TimeWarp controls do not work in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E. This is intended\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u0022R2\u0022 refers to the right mouse button\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf the above Keybind Maps have an error, please respond in this thread.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf a keybind is not working as intended in-game, please submit \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/forms/2-ksp2br/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ea bug report\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ChadDude","CreatedById":229755,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-12T00:24:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYoo thats amazing, congrats the the artist!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Heretic391","CreatedById":66101,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-12T00:27:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVery handy and cool looking \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:awe:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/awe.png\u0022 title=\u0022:awe:\u0022\u003EThank you.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow71","CreatedById":210112,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-12T01:29:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow we just need to be able to bring these up in game...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James M","CreatedById":167171,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-12T02:37:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYa\u2019ll are on a roll. Thanks for this! Hopefully we\u2019ll be able to access these in game soon and then we\u2019ll be really cookin\u2019\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Space Peacock","CreatedById":224498,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-12T03:13:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003Eeveryone liked that\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-12T05:29:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah about that... Anyone managed to get the Kerbal helmet lights on? Since it\u0027s listed here, I\u0027d assume it should work but\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224301722\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022218360\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221689121128\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022225122\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dakota\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Dakota said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022R2\u0022 refers to the right mouse button\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI suppose the more common acronym is RMB.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-07-12T05:31:36Z\u0022 title=\u002207/12/2023 05:31  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 12, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by The Aziz\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lyneira","CreatedById":149515,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-12T09:49:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe control for resetting trim (alt-x) appears to be absent from the Flight keymap.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-07-12T09:50:10Z\u0022 title=\u002207/12/2023 09:50  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 12, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Lyneira\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LoSBoL","CreatedById":174038,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-12T10:08:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m missing the controls for a couple of things in flight;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-Changing your FOV, done with alt \u002B middle mouse buttons scroll in KSP1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-Changing the POV, in KSP1 you could focus on a part as the center of the POV by right clicking the part and selecting as POV. Currently in KSP2 there is no means of doing this outside the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E and the POV is set on the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d really like to see those controls back \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-12T23:59:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis reminds me of those keyboard stickers for Excel in the 90s.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...which after a quick Google search I found they still make today.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut anyway it made me think, if the controls were on the keys themselves you could print these on sticker paper and make a KSP2 keyboard.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Example of the excel stickers)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002261Tz58fklDL._AC_.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002251.00\u0022 height=\u0022255\u0022 width=\u0022500\u0022 src=\u0022https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/61Tz58fklDL._AC_.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-07-13T00:00:36Z\u0022 title=\u002207/13/2023 12:00  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 13, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Superfluous J\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow71","CreatedById":210112,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-13T00:49:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224301974\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022218360\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221689206394\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n48 minutes ago, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis reminds me of those keyboard stickers for Excel in the 90s.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...which after a quick Google search I found they still make today.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut anyway it made me think, if the controls were on the keys themselves you could print these on sticker paper and make a KSP2 keyboard.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Example of the excel stickers)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EReveal hidden contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca data-fileid=\u0022undefined\u0022 href=\u0022https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/61Tz58fklDL._AC_.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u002261Tz58fklDL._AC_.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002251.00\u0022 height=\u0022255\u0022 width=\u0022500\u0022 src=\u0022https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/61Tz58fklDL._AC_.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInclude one with every purchase of a jeb plushie.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mattihase","CreatedById":73161,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-13T15:52:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224301769\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022218360\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221689139766\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Aziz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/12/2023 at 6:29 AM, The Aziz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI suppose the more common acronym is RMB.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr Mouse_1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nR2\u0027s a very odd thing to call it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224301722\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022218360\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221689121128\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022225122\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dakota\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/12/2023 at 1:18 AM, Dakota said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe TimeWarp controls do not work in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E. This is intended\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWill there be a way to at least timewarp to morning when launching from the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E? A frustration I\u0027ve kept running in to with the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E is trying to iterate on builds launching from/reverting to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E but because time advances in there now it seems harder to avoid being stuck launching at night if you stay in there building for too long.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat or an option to turn off time passing in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LoSBoL","CreatedById":174038,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-15T09:26:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnother missing,\u00A0 which button activates the Kerbal parachute?\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:awe:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/awe.png\u0022 title=\u0022:awe:\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-15T10:41:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey don\u0027t have those yet (it was mentioned somewhere officially)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m still asking for the EVA lights though, do they work or not despite having a keybind?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James M","CreatedById":167171,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-15T12:12:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cs\u003EJust started a new campaign and this reminded me of something thats been really frustrating me. Anyone know how to translate the camera in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003Evab\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E independently of the parts placed? In Ksp1 I could move my camera up and then drag the rocket up to the height I wanted it at, but now I have to move the root part up to the top of my screen then right click it to move my camera up. Even more so if I\u2019m building a larger sized vehicle.\u00A0\u003C/s\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI FIGURED IT OUT GUYS! Lol just hold your mouse wheel in and move your mouse up and down. Ugh that\u2019s been bothering me so much.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nWhat about focusing the camera on a different part on my rocket?\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd is there a way to preview extended engine bells in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E? I want to see the length of my vacuum engine in full before I consider putting on things like legs on a lander.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-07-15T12:22:24Z\u0022 title=\u002207/15/2023 12:22  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 15, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by James M\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-15T12:21:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224302760\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022218360\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221689423164\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022167171\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022James M\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, James M said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust started a new campaign and this reminded me of something thats been really frustrating me. Anyone know how to translate the camera in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003Evab\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E independently of the parts placed? In Ksp1 I could move my camera up and then drag the rocket up to the height I wanted it at, but now I have to move the root part up to the top of my screen then right click it to move my camera up. Even more so if I\u2019m building a larger sized vehicle.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nAlso what about focusing the camera on a different part on my rocket?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHold middle click and drag the camera up or down.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMiddle click on a part to focus on it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James M","CreatedById":167171,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-15T12:23:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224302771\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022218360\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221689423696\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022228085\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spicat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Spicat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHold middle click and drag the camera up or down.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMiddle click on a part to focus on it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks so much ^-^\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MechBFP","CreatedById":184845,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-15T14:03:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224302760\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022218360\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221689423164\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022167171\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022James M\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, James M said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI FIGURED IT OUT GUYS! Lol just hold your mouse wheel in and move your mouse up and down. Ugh that\u2019s been bothering me so much.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat has also been bothering me, I\u2019ll have to give that a try. Although with the camera auto refocusing on parts against my will half the time, it won\u2019t help much I am thinking.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LoSBoL","CreatedById":174038,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-15T14:26:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224302740\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022218360\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221689417665\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Aziz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, The Aziz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey don\u0027t have those yet (it was mentioned somewhere officially)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m still asking for the EVA lights though, do they work or not despite having a keybind?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI knew, like with my earlier poat about FOV and POV it was my cheeky way of saying I\u0027m missing these features.\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:blush2:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/blush2.png\u0022 title=\u0022:blush2:\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AlexE","CreatedById":229979,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-19T10:34:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you Intercept Games, this is very helpful. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022^_^\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_happy.png\u0022 title=\u0022^_^\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Laxez","CreatedById":216956,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-21T06:52:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould you add a shortcut to open and close the solar panels and another one for the antennas?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-21T12:39:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n[snip]\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224304363\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022218360\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221689922343\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022216956\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Laxez\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, Laxez said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould you add a shortcut to open and close the solar panels and another one for the antennas?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s a button in the action group panel for solar panels. The rest you can add to your own action groups.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-07-21T20:44:14Z\u0022 title=\u002207/21/2023 08:44  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Jul 21\u0022\u003EJuly 21, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Vanamonde\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"adsii1970","CreatedById":89014,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-21T12:54:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224304363\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022218360\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221689922343\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022216956\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Laxez\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Laxez said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould you add a shortcut to open and close the solar panels and another one for the antennas?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis already exists; It can be done using action groups 1 through 0 (yes, you can have ten different things \u0022automated\u0022 using action groups). You\u0027ll have to set them up in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSince the original KSP, I pretty much have specific keys I use for different things. That way, I never worry about accidentally deploying anything too soon. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003ETrial and error is always the best teacher! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:blush:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_embarrassed.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:blush:\u0022\u003E\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JPR","CreatedById":199326,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-21T19:42:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#f9f9f9;color:#2d3134;font-size:15px;\u0022\u003EAs has been mentioned- \u0022in KSP1 you could focus on a part as the center of the POV by right clicking the part and selecting as POV. \u00A0Currently in KSP2 there is no means of doing this outside the\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cabbr style=\u0022border-bottom-style:none;border-bottom-width:medium;\u0022 title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:rgb(249,249,249);\u0022\u003E\u0022 \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr style=\u0022border-bottom-style:none;border-bottom-width:medium;\u0022 title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:rgb(249,249,249);\u0022\u003ECan you fix this and provided a per part clink and information and not for the whole vessel as the list gets way too long! \u00A0 \u00A0Also the UI for the popup menu is way too\u00A0large.\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}